The paper deals with lossless compression, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also introduces the concept of an optimal compressor and shows that it works in probabilistic polynomial time, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses distributed compression, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS) and data compression (cs.DC). Finally, the paper mentions the Slepian-Wolf theorem, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CR).
